SIMPLE: prodigally
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Prodigally
<hw>Prod"i*gal*ly</hw>, <pos>adv.</pos> <def>In a prodigal manner; with
profusion of expense; extravagantly; wasteful; profusely; lavishly;
<as>as, an estate <ex>prodigally</ex> dissipated</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Nature not bounteous now, but lavish grows;⟦br⟧
Our paths with flowers she <qex>prodigally</qex> strows.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Prodigate</ent>⟦br⟧
